{
  "designRationale": {
    "layoutDecisions": "The screen uses a vertical layout to present settings in a clear, scannable list.  The top app bar provides navigation and context, while the bottom navigation bar ensures consistent access to other app sections.  Spacing between list items is consistent (24px) for readability and to create visual breathing room.  Padding is added at the top and bottom (48px) to avoid a cramped feel on smaller screens.",
    "userFlowReasoning": "The user flow is straightforward: users see their current settings, tap to modify them (or tap options such as 'Delete account' or 'Log Out'), and receive feedback after each action. The primary actions (changing personal details and account deletion) are clearly highlighted and placed prominently within the settings list.  Account deletion includes a confirmation dialog to prevent accidental deletions.",
    "componentChoices": "The `appbar` component provides a consistent top navigation bar. `list-item` components display each setting with its value or action. The `Button` component is used for primary actions and the Bottom Navigation bar, `Bottom navigation`, provides persistent navigation between core app sections.  A dialog component will be employed for account deletion confirmation.",
    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is established through a combination of layout, typography, and color.  Main actions are represented by buttons with clear labels, which receive more prominent styling. Setting titles are presented using appropriate text styles (e.g., `Title/Medium`) to clearly denote their importance in relation to the content beneath them. Consistent use of color styles and typography maintain a visual consistency and enhance readability."
  }
}
